hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I'd like to tell you about a change of address bentyl reddit Malala Yousafzai says one of the most difficult things about being at school in England is that she can never be a “normal girl”. She is doomed to be the super-good education campaigner who was shot in the head: “In Pakistan, I was just Malala.” Whether she wins the Nobel Peace Prize tomorrow – and no one could deserve it more – she will never again be just Malala. Yet, by being so extraordinary, in her courage and her eloquence, this 16-year-old may enable millions of girls to go to school, and just to be normal. Her achievements are humbling – and her father was right. Educate your daughters, they are amazing.
